South Africa Plans to Start State Rail-Price Regulator, Business Day Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-06-02T05:36:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/south-africa-plans-to-start-state-rail-price-regulator-business-day-says.html
South Africa  plans to set up a
regulator that will monitor rail prices in the country where
Transnet Ltd., the state ports and rail operator, is a monopoly,
Business Day reported, citing Deputy Transport Minister Jeremy
Cronin.  The agency would complement the Rail Safety Regulator and
would help relieve bottlenecks in freight transportation,
especially between Johannesburg and the port city of Durban, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  